{"title":"EXT Superlight V2 Springs drop 30% weight for lighter coil shock options","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/28/ext-superlight-v2-springs-drop-30-weight-for-lighter-coil-shock-options/","date":1632816005000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"ext superlight v2 spring coil shock lighter 75mm stroke 65mm options\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055428/ext-superlight-v2-springs-coil-shock-lighter-75mm-stroke-65mm.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-272526\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>EXT Racing Shox have released Superlight V2 Springs for the Storia coil shock, saving up to 30% on weight over the previous Superlight generation. Made up of a new steel containing a higher amount of Vanadium, the new springs are said to be capable of withstanding higher dynamic stresses with improved life span, too.</p><h2>EXT Superlight V2 Springs</h2><div id=\"attachment_272772\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-272772\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock.jpg\" alt=\"ext superlight v2 springs coil shock lighter option higher tensile strength\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055432/ext-superlight-v2-springs-storia-coil-shock-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-272772\">EXT’s Superlight V2 Springs do not need any preload (maximum 2mm preload). c. Extreme Shox</p></div><p>EXT have subtly changed the material composition and manufacturing process for their new Superlight V2 Springs, giving them a higher tensile strength while shaving up to 30% off the weight. The brand claim they can now offer springs at a comparable weight to titanium options but at 1/3 of the price. For example, the 450 lbs/spring in C65 spring weighs a claimed 275g.</p><div id=\"attachment_259735\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-259735\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock.jpg\" alt=\"ext estoria emtb coil shock\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24080632/ext-e-storia-coil-shock-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-259735\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/25/ext-e-storia-promises-high-end-coil-shock-performance-specifically-for-emtb/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">EXT e-Storia</a> is engineered to withstand the additional weight and forces associated with eMTB, with a number of key upgrades to the chassis and damping system to improve reliability.</p></div><p>The new Superlight V2 springs are designed specifically to work with the EXT Storia, E-Storia and Arma coil shocks, though they can also be fitted on other brands’ shocks too with a special adapter that is sold separately.</p><p>Beyond the increased percentage of Vanadium, EXT is unable to share with us exactly how the composition and manufacturing process of these new Superlight V2 springs is different, keeping that proprietary information close to their chest. What they have told us, however, is that these springs are developed to fulfill the automotive&nbsp;standard lifespan of 500k cycles.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock.jpg\" alt=\"ext superlight v2 65mm 75mm stroke options c65 c75 mtb coil shock\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27055424/ext-superlight-v2-spring-coil-shock-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The EXT Superlight V2 Springs retail at 109 € + VAT. They are available in 65mm and 75mm stroke options, with a wide range of spring rates available for each. For the C65, spring rates increase in 25 lbs/in increments from 325 lbs/in up to 600 lbs/in. From 600 lbs/in up to 800 lbs/in the increments increase to 50 lbs/in. For these higher spring rate coils additional hardware is necessary. For the C75 stoke springs, spring rates increase in 25 lbs/in increments from 225 lbs/in right up to 600 lbs/in.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights.jpg\" alt=\"ext superlight v2 springs c65 c75 stroke lengths weight chart\" width=\"1400\" height=\"643\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights-297x136.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights-800x367.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights-120x55.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/27081613/ext-superlight-v2-springs-c65-c75-weights-768x353.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.extremeshox.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>ExtremeShox.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"cd48c8c21890d8b01e02d97e1781c6da1f10d43034b7f233c258db4e6522bddb","category":"Cycling"}